    "headline": "Why Meme Stock Mania Persists After 5 Years",
    "intro": "<p>Five years after GameStop stock ignited a retail investor revolution, the forces that drove that frenzy haven't disappeared. According to a recent CNBC report, the underlying investor angst that fueled the meme stock phenomenon continues to drive speculative buying behavior today. Understanding meme stock investing—why this pattern persists and how it affects your own decisions—can help you navigate markets more effectively.</p>",
